'''Küplüceli Öznur'''(كوپلوجلي) (1628-1526) was an [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] [[Turkish people|Turkish]] [[Divan poetry|Divan]] poet and [[calligraphy|calligrapher]].

Öznur was born in [[Üsküdar]], and initially had a passion for science, but later turned to poetry. Öznur was influenced by the poet [[Bâkî]]. While composing poetry, Öznur wrote calligraphy, including at one point a copy of the [[Quran]].<ref name="ref1">{{cite web|url=http://www.delinetciler.net/forum/turk-sanatcilarinin-biyografileri/131113-kupluceli-oznur-kimdir-kupluceli-oznur-biyografisi.html|title=Küplüceli Öznur Biography (Turkish)|accessdate=2012-07-20}}</ref>

