'''Gholam Hossein Amirkhani'''(استاد غلامحسین امیرخانی) is a [[Persian people|Persian]] [[calligrapher]], born in 1939 in [[Taleghan]], [[Iran]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.caroun.com/Calligraphy/Iran/QolamhosseinAmirkhani/QolamhosseinAmirkhani1.html |title=Calligraphist: Qolamhossein Amir Khani |work=caroun.com |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6T02RLKLm?url=http://www.caroun.com/Calligraphy/Iran/QolamhosseinAmirkhani/QolamhosseinAmirkhani1.html |archivedate=1 October 2014 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>

In 2014, he held his first solo exhibition in 15 years, showing his latest works in Tehran's Sareban Gallery. Prices for works for sale at the exhibition ranged from $2,500 to $11,500.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.iran-daily.com/News/55963.html|title=Amirkhani displays calligraphy|website=www.iran-daily.com|access-date=2017-01-22}}</ref> In 2015, he the Iran Society for the Appreciation of Cultural Works and Dignitaries in Tehran paid tribute to Amirkhani on the occasion of his 75th birthday.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://financialtribune.com/articles/art-and-culture/9765/amirkhani-synonymous-with-calligraphy|title=Amirkhani Synonymous With Calligraphy|date=2015-01-26|newspaper=Financial Tribune|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-22}}</ref>

