'''Maulana Azhar''' (died 1475) was a  [[Persian people|Persian]] [[Calligraphy|calligrapher]]. 

Azhar was trained by [[Mir Ali Tabrizi]] and worked for [[Shah Rukh (Timurid dynasty)|Shah Rukh]] in the [[Timurid dynasty|Timurid court]]. His calligraphy primarily used the [[Nastaʿlīq script]].<ref name="ref1">{{cite web|url=http://www.alamahabibi.com/English%20Articles/Calligraphy.htm|title=History of Persian Calligraphy|accessdate=2012-07-19}}</ref>

